This file documents the fix applied to telegram.rs.

Problem:
  markdown_to_telegram_html() escapes all '<' characters to '&lt;',
  including valid Telegram HTML tags like <b>, <tg-spoiler> that the
  LLM outputs directly per the system prompt instructions.

Fix:
  Added try_telegram_html_tag_len() helper that recognises whitelisted
  Telegram HTML tags and returns their byte length. In the inline
  character loop, before falling through to HTML escaping, we check
  if the current '<' starts a valid tag and pass it through verbatim.

Whitelisted tags (open + close):
  b, i, u, s, code, pre, tg-spoiler, a

Non-whitelisted tags (e.g. <tag>, <script>) are still escaped.
